Commit Message:
v1.0.0 release

Co-authored-by: Jonas Krüger Svensson <jonas-ks@hotmail.com>
bugfix: Reorder imports to prevent uninstalled libraries from breaking the middleware
Add example of celery tracing ID output
Add access control expose headers test

Update mypy config (#2)

* Simplify test workflow
* Update docstring and comments, to separate middleware and extension features
* Enable mypy strict mode and fix type hinting issues
* Add coverage to dev dependencies
Make coverage dev dependency conditional on Python 3.10
Add docs on how to change middleware settings
Add section on setting up logging
Add py.typed to support type checking
Specify which folder to include when building the package
Dont crop correlation id in logs by default

chore: Remove workflow cache step

Caching just the pre-commit installation seems redundant
chore: Add Python 3.11-alpha5 to test matrix
chore: Remove pytest-cov in favor of just coverage
chore: Document how to handle server errors
Convert headers to raw headers to handle the case of duplicate header keys
chore: add typing for return value in README

docs: add example for structlog integration

Fixes #24
Add test for multiple headers with same name

refactor(middleware): Only add access-control-expose-headers when returning CID header

This is a non-change since a CID should always have been generated on the way in.
chore: Bump package version from 1.1.2 to 1.1.3
chore: Bump package version from 1.1.3 to 1.1.4
Add CorrelationIDFilter to allow string-based configuration
Update docs to use CorrelationIDFilter as string
Update test fixture to use CorrelationIDFilter as string
Change case of CorrelationIdFilter for consistency with CorrelationIdMiddleware
Replace celery_tracing_id_filter factory function with CeleryTracingIdsFilter class

chore: Add sourcery config-file to .gitignore

I personally use the Sourcery Pycharm plugin
and want to specify for it not to suggest
cleanups that break compatibility for supported
versions (e.g., walrus operator upgrades).

This doesn't seem like something worth keeping in
version control though, so opting for .gitignore'ing
it.
chore: Add metadata indicating support for Python 3.11
chore: Update mypy's python version to 3.7
chore: Bump package version to v2.0.0

feat: Rework request ID generation and validation

Add concept of `generator`, `validator`, and `transformer`
to make request ID generation, validation, and cleaning
fully configurable.
tests: Add and refactor tests for new class variables
docs: Add section on middleware configuration
chore: Update pre-commit hooks and black preview flag

Use the default header name in docs

The docs switch to using X-Correlation-ID in examples but X-Request-ID
is the default value. This change fixes that inconsistency.
fix: Add starlette to package dependencies

chore: Add fastapi versions to test matrix

Ideally we'll want to implement all supported Starlette versions
in the test matrix, but this should do as an intermediate step.

To do Starlette, we'll need to rewrite the test code first.
chore: Reset cached venv and correct test workflow
chore: Add Python 3.11 to test matrix

Added customizable generator options to celery extension to better match capabilities of the correlation id middleware
* Added optional "header_key" param to asgi_correlation_id.extensions.celery.load_correlation_id
* Added optional "generator" param to asgi_correlation_id.extensions.celery.load_correlation_id
* Added optional "generator" param to asgi_correlation_id.extensions.celery.load_celery_current_and_parent_ids

chore: Rename publish workflow

`publish.yml` is more in line with other
snok packages, and just simpler.

Standardized the signatures for CorrelationIdFilter/CeleryTracingIdsFilter and standardized the string trimming process for the filtering logic
* changed type from int to Optional[int] for optional parameter 'uuid_length' in CeleryTracingIdsFilter
* changed default value from 32 to None for optional parameter 'uuid_length' in CeleryTracingIdsFilter
* created and utilized function `_trim_string` to standardize string trimming logic in filters
* added test to test string trimming for CeleryTracingIdsFilter
* added test to ensure the default behavior of the new filter matched the behavior of the old filter.  This assumes default generators are used

expanded `load_celery_current_and_parent_ids` to be able to utilize the internally generated celery_id
* Added optional argument `use_internal_celery_task_id` to `load_celery_current_and_parent_ids`
* When `use_internal_celery_task_id` is set to True, the internal celery task ID will be used and the generator function will be ignored
* Updated README with information on this new argument
docs: Clarify what broker ID refers to
chore: Remove python 3.8 syntax from tests
chore: Update pre-commit hooks and fix linting issues

Add contextvars to package `__init__`

I've also added `celery_current_id` and `celery_parent_id`.

Add support for updating request header value

Closes #64.

Remove Access-Control-Expose-Headers response header

As discussed in https://github.com/snok/asgi-correlation-id/discussions/66, handling CORS should better be left to a specialized middleware.
Add information about CORS to the README
Fix CORS middleware setup in README examples
breaking: Change the default value of `update_request_header`
Add support for log filter default value

Use new header value in failed validation warning

We should use the newly generated header value in the failed validation
warning message as using the original header value might be a security risk.
See the discussion here – https://github.com/snok/asgi-correlation-id/discussions/69.
chore: Update pre-commit hooks and lockfile

chore: Update supported Python versions

Drops 3.7 and adds 3.12
tests: Fix broken test by ignoring Python 3.12 warnings
